Like over midnatt. Kanskje du leser denne sms-en.
Utenfor: En ungdomsgjeng passerer med klirrende poser,
de høylytte stemmene forsvinner inn i natta.
Hvis du står oppe på knausen og lurer på hvor jeg er i kveld,
drikker mer sprit enn du tåler for ikke å dra bekymringene over i det nye året,
så sender jeg opp ei enslig rakett over Brosundet,
som knuses til et rødt perleregn som slukner og dør på den svarte vinterhimmelen.

Quote: http://theboringstore.blogspot.com/2008/12/boring-store-presenterer-fra-notatboka.html
Levi Weaver "You Are Home" from Paper Beats Rock on Vimeo.

So, so you think you can tell
Heaven from Hell,
Blue skys from pain.
Can you tell a green field
From a cold steel rail?
A smile from a veil?
Do you think you can tell?

And did they get you to trade
Your heros for ghosts?
Hot ashes for trees?
Hot air for a cool breeze?
Cold comfort for change?
And did you exchange
A walk on part in the war
For a lead role in a cage?

How I wish, how I wish you were here.
We're just two lost souls
Swimming in a fish bowl,
Year after year,
Running over the same old ground.
What have we found?
The same old fears.
Wish you were here.

I get near...
but I never seem
to reach
you

Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

Last Friday I punched in the arm (-10 points). In September I helped across the street (6 points). In May I stole 's purse (-30 points). Last Monday I broke 's X-Box (-12 points). In October I put gum in 's hair (-12 points).

Overall, I've been naughty (-58 points). For Christmas I deserve a moldy sandwich!

Sincerely,
triumphant1
